Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive analysis document.

## Analysis: Starlight CSS and Component Styling Classes

### Overview

Starlight uses scoped styles within individual Astro components and global CSS files organized by layer (starlight.core, starlight.components, starlight.content, starlight.utils). The Card component uses dynamic color variables based on position, the Hero component uses grid-based layout with responsive styling, and sidebar uses CSS custom properties for theming.

---

## 1. Card Component Styling

### Component File
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/chkit/davao/apps/docs/node_modules/@astrojs/starlight/user-components/Card.astro`

### Class Names to Target

| Element | CSS Class | Scoped Layer | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|--------------|---------|
| Card container | `.card` | `starlight.components` | Main card wrapper, uses `sl-flex` |
| Card title section | `.title` | `starlight.components` | Heading area with icon and text |
| Card icon | `.icon` | `starlight.components` | Icon styling (child of `.card .icon`) |
| Card body | `.body` | `starlight.components` | Content area |
| Card grid wrapper | `.card-grid` | `starlight.components` | Container for multiple cards |

### CSS Variables and Color Cycling

The Card component implements cycling colors based on position (every 4th card):

```css
.card {
    --sl-card-border: var(--sl-color-purple);
    --sl-card-bg: var(--sl-color-purple-low);
}

.card:nth-child(4n + 1) {
    --sl-card-border: var(--sl-color-orange);
    --sl-card-bg: var(--sl-color-orange-low);
}

.card:nth-child(4n + 3) {
    --sl-card-border: var(--sl-color-green);
    --sl-card-bg: var(--sl-color-green-low);
}

.card:nth-child(4n + 4) {
    --sl-card-border: var(--sl-color-red);
    --sl-card-bg: var(--sl-color-red-low);
}

.card:nth-child(4n + 5) {
    --sl-card-border: var(--sl-color-blue);
    --sl-card-bg: var(--sl-color-blue-low);
}
```

### Specific Selectors for Overriding

To override card colors, target:
- `.card:nth-child(4n + 1)` - Orange (1st, 5th, 9th, etc.)
- `.card:nth-child(4n + 3)` - Green (3rd, 7th, 11th, etc.)
- `.card:nth-child(4n + 4)` - Red (4th, 8th, 12th, etc.)
- `.card:nth-child(4n + 5)` - Blue (5th variant, if it cascades with +1)
- `.card` (default) - Purple

### Card Icon Styling
```css
.card .icon {
    border: 1px solid var(--sl-card-border);
    background-color: var(--sl-card-bg);
    padding: 0.2em;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
}
```

### CardGrid Styling
```css
.card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 100%;
    gap: 1rem;
}

@media (min-width: 50rem) {
    .card-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1.5rem;
    }
    .stagger {
        --stagger-height: 5rem;
        padding-bottom: var(--stagger-height);
    }
    .stagger > :global(*):nth-child(2n) {
        transform: translateY(var(--stagger-height));
    }
}
```

---

## 2. Hero Component Styling

### Component File
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/chkit/davao/apps/docs/node_modules/@astrojs/starlight/components/Hero.astro`

### Class Names to Target

| Element | CSS Class | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Hero container | `.hero` | Main hero section wrapper (CSS Grid) |
| Hero image/HTML | `.hero > img`, `.hero > .hero-html` | Image or custom HTML content |
| Stack container | `.stack` | Flex container for title, tagline, actions |
| Copy section | `.copy` | Title and tagline wrapper |
| Tagline text | `.tagline` | Subtitle text |
| Actions buttons | `.actions` | Button container for CTA buttons |
| Main heading | `h1` (inside hero) | Page title (id="__sl_page_title__") |

### Hero Layout Selectors

```css
.hero {
    display: grid;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
}

.hero > img,
.hero > .hero-html {
    object-fit: contain;
    width: min(70%, 20rem);
    height: auto;
    margin-inline: auto;
}

.stack {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, calc(1.5rem + 1vw), 2rem);
    text-align: center;
}

.copy {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
}

.copy > * {
    max-width: 50ch;
}

h1 {
    font-size: clamp(var(--sl-text-3xl), calc(0.25rem + 5vw), var(--sl-text-6xl));
    line-height: var(--sl-line-height-headings);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
}

.tagline {
    font-size: clamp(var(--sl-text-base), calc(0.0625rem + 2vw), var(--sl-text-xl));
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
}

.actions {
    gap: 1rem 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
}
```

### Responsive (Desktop: 50rem+)

```css
@media (min-width: 50rem) {
    .hero {
        grid-template-columns: 7fr 4fr;
        gap: 3%;
        padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, calc(1rem + 10vmin), 10rem);
    }

    .hero > img,
    .hero > .hero-html {
        order: 2;
        width: min(100%, 25rem);
    }

    .stack {
        text-align: start;
    }

    .copy {
        align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .actions {
        justify-content: flex-start;
    }
}
```

### Action Buttons

Buttons inside `.actions` use the `LinkButton` component with these classes:

```css
.sl-link-button {
    align-items: center;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-radius: 999rem;
    display: inline-flex;
    font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
    gap: 0.5em;
    line-height: 1.1875;
    outline-offset: 0.25rem;
    padding: 0.4375rem 1.125rem;
    text-decoration: none;
}

.sl-link-button.primary {
    background: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
    border-color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
    color: var(--sl-color-black);
}

.sl-link-button.secondary {
    border-color: inherit;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
}

.sl-link-button.minimal {
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
    padding-inline: 0;
}
```

---

## 3. Sidebar Component Styling

### Component Files
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/chkit/davao/apps/docs/node_modules/@astrojs/starlight/components/Sidebar.astro` (wrapper)
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/chkit/davao/apps/docs/node_modules/@astrojs/starlight/components/SidebarSublist.astro` (actual styling)

### Class Names to Target

| Element | CSS Class | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Sidebar list | `ul` | Main list container (`top-level` for root) |
| List item | `li` | Individual menu items |
| Nested lists | `ul ul` | Nested item styling |
| Link item | `a` | Sidebar links |
| Group label | `.group-label` | Expandable group title |
| Large text | `.large` | Font size for top-level and group labels |
| Caret icon | `.caret` | Expand/collapse chevron icon |
| Summary element | `summary` | Expandable group header |
| Current page | `[aria-current='page']` | Active/selected item styling |

### Sidebar Styling Selectors

```css
ul {
    --sl-sidebar-item-padding-inline: 0.5rem;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
}

li {
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
}

ul ul li {
    margin-inline-start: var(--sl-sidebar-item-padding-inline);
    border-inline-start: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline-light);
    padding-inline-start: var(--sl-sidebar-item-padding-inline);
}

.large {
    font-size: var(--sl-text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
}

.top-level > li + li {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
}

summary {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 0.2em var(--sl-sidebar-item-padding-inline);
    line-height: 1.4;
    cursor: pointer;
    user-select: none;
}

summary::marker,
summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
}

.caret {
    transition: transform 0.2s ease-in-out;
    flex-shrink: 0;
}

:global([dir='rtl']) .caret {
    transform: rotateZ(180deg);
}

[open] > summary .caret {
    transform: rotateZ(90deg);
}

a {
    display: block;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    padding: 0.3em var(--sl-sidebar-item-padding-inline);
    line-height: 1.4;
}

a:hover,
a:focus {
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
}

[aria-current='page'],
[aria-current='page']:hover,
[aria-current='page']:focus {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--sl-color-text-invert);
    background-color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
}

a > *:not(:last-child),
.group-label > *:not(:last-child) {
    margin-inline-end: 0.25em;
}
```

### Responsive (Desktop: 50rem+)

```css
@media (min-width: 50rem) {
    .top-level > li + li {
        margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }
    .large {
        font-size: var(--sl-text-base);
    }
    a {
        font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
    }
}
```

---

## 4. Icon Styling

### Component File
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/chkit/davao/apps/docs/node_modules/@astrojs/starlight/user-components/Icon.astro`

### SVG Icon Class Names

```css
svg {
    color: var(--sl-icon-color);
    font-size: var(--sl-icon-size, 1em);
    width: 1em;
    height: 1em;
}
```

The Icon component accepts:
- `color` prop → sets `--sl-icon-color` CSS variable
- `size` prop → sets `--sl-icon-size` CSS variable

---

## 5. Color Variables (Global)

All components rely on these CSS custom properties defined in `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/chkit/davao/apps/docs/node_modules/@astrojs/starlight/style/props.css`:

### Card Colors
```css
--sl-color-purple: hsl(281, 82%, 63%);
--sl-color-purple-low: hsl(281, 39%, 22%);
--sl-color-orange: hsl(41, 82%, 63%);
--sl-color-orange-low: hsl(41, 39%, 22%);
--sl-color-green: hsl(101, 82%, 63%);
--sl-color-green-low: hsl(101, 39%, 22%);
--sl-color-blue: hsl(234, 100%, 60%);
--sl-color-blue-low: hsl(234, 54%, 20%);
--sl-color-red: hsl(339, 82%, 63%);
--sl-color-red-low: hsl(339, 39%, 22%);
```

### Text Colors
```css
--sl-color-white: hsl(0, 0%, 100%);
--sl-color-gray-2: hsl(224, 6%, 77%);
--sl-color-text-accent: var(--sl-color-accent-high);
--sl-color-text-invert: var(--sl-color-accent-low);
```

### Background Colors
```css
--sl-color-black: hsl(224, 10%, 10%);
--sl-color-hairline-light: var(--sl-color-gray-5);
--sl-color-bg-sidebar: var(--sl-color-gray-6);
```

---

## 6. CSS Layers and Specificity

All Starlight styles are organized in layers (for override control):

```
@layer starlight.base
@layer starlight.core
@layer starlight.components
@layer starlight.content
@layer starlight.utils
```

To override with your own styles, you should:
1. Create your styles AFTER importing Starlight
2. Target the same selectors
3. Or use `@layer overrides { }` to create a layer that comes after starlight

